29/05/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- Prosecutors announced on Monday (May 28th) that two people have been charged in connection with weekend drownings on the Lousios River in southern Greece. 
The co-owners of a travel company that organised the hiking excursion face charges of murder due to negligence. 
One of them served as the guide during the ill-fated trip. 
Six tourists in the group were swept away and killed as they tried to cross the river on Saturday. 
(ANA-MPA, ERT - 28/05/07)
